istory and cultures of the African Diaspora, the Muslims have been largely ignored. Servants of Allah-a Choice 1999 Outstanding Academic Title-illuminates the role of Islam in the lives of both individual practitioners and communities, and shows that though the religion did not survive in the Americas in its orthodox form, its mark can be found in certain religions, traditions, and artistic creations of people of African descent. This 15th anniversary edition has been updated to include new materials and analysis, a review of developments in the field, prospects for new research, and new illustrations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAfrican AmericansxHistoryyTo 1863. 0aMuslims, BlackxHistoryxAmerican. 0aMuslims, BlackzAmericanxHistory. 0aMuslims, BlackzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSlavesxReligious lifexHistoryxAmerica. 0aSlavesxReligious lifezAmericaxHistory. 0aSlavesxReligious lifezUnited StatesxHistory. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh1 aDiouf, Sylviane A., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479844470423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479844470/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles